The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 16 April is 41,626 (4,817.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 11 April, there were 148 new confirmed cases (17.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 April, there were 128 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 16% (20 extra cases).
